===Noun===
{{en-noun|rights of first refusal}}

# {{lb|en|legal}} A [[provision]] in a [[contract]] that permits a [[party]] to that contract or another named party to have an [[opportunity]] to [[purchase]], [[use]], or otherwise [[obtain]] a specified object before it is offered to any other party.
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1985|author=Richard Lourie|title=First Loyalty|isbn=9780151312870|pageurl=http://books.google.ca/books?id=Majycqgv4hgC&q=%22right+of+first+refusal%22+subject:%22fiction%22&dq=%22right+of+first+refusal%22+subject:%22fiction%22&lr=&as_brr=0&client=firefox-a|page=258
|passage="Well," said the publisher, "does our last contract with whoever it is that represents Shar give us the '''right of first refusal''' on his next book?"}}

